          "projects_submitted": 0,
          "name": "Build with Gemma",
          "tagline": "Bengaluru AI Sprint",
          "location": "Ramaiah Institute of Technology, MSRIT Post, M S R Nagar, Mathikere, Bengaluru, Karnataka, India",
          "judges": [],
          "cover_img": "https://assets.devfolio.co/hackathons/9ca9be8320484be0840ad2f4771bc4f9/assets/cover/957.png",
          "desc": "Build with Gemma : Bengaluru AI Sprint is a one-day, in-person  hackathon organized by Heapify Global Community in collaboration with the  IEEE Computational Intelligence Society (IEEE CIS) Bangalore Chapter  and the  Department of Information Science, MS Ramaiah Institute of Technology (MSRIT)  as part of the Build with Gemma initiative.\n\nThis hackathon brings together students, developers,  founders, and AI professionals to build innovative, real world applications powered by Gemma 4 . Participants will collaborate in teams to design and develop Gemma AI solutions  that address challenges in the SME & Financial AI domain.\n\nChallenges & Track of Hackathon - \n\nTrack 1: Gemma SME Cashflow Copilot\n\nBuild an AI powered financial assistant using Gemma that helps SMEs forecast cash flow, identify liquidity risks, automate invoice follow-ups, optimize payment schedules, and recommend actionable financial decisions.\n\nTrack 2: Gemma Financial Compliance & Risk Triage\n\nDevelop an intelligent compliance assistant that analyzes transactions, onboarding documents, and financial records to detect anomalies, assess risk, summarize findings, and generate compliance-ready reports for review teams.\n\nTrack 3: Gemma SME Growth & Advisory Agent\n\nCreate an AI business advisor that empowers SMEs with data-driven insights for pricing, revenue forecasting, supplier management, collections, operational planning, and strategic business growth through conversational AI.\n\nThroughout the event, participants will receive guidance from experienced mentors, interact with industry experts, and present their projects before an expert judging panel. The event is designed to encourage rapid prototyping, technical innovation, and practical problem-solving using Google' s latest open AI models .",
